member.remarks:
Index is used by the C# compiler to support the new index syntax

int[] someArray = new int[5] { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 } ;
int lastElement = someArray[^1]; // lastElement = 5

Range is used by the C# compiler to support the range syntax.

int[] someArray = new int[5] { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 };
int[] subArray1 = someArray[0..2]; // { 1, 2 }
int[] subArray2 = someArray[1..^0]; // { 2, 3, 4, 5 }

member.return:
The index of the element whose key matches ;
or if none match, the index of the element whose key is closest and lower;
or if all elements' keys are higher, -1.

(Equivalently: If none match, 1 less than the index where inserting an element with the given  would keep the list sorted)
